    "description": "<p>\r\n\t&quot;WPG Holdings&rdquo; as Asia&rsquo;s No. 1 Electronics Distributor, was founded on 09 November 2005 (TSE:3702). WPG Holdings operating through seven leading semiconductor distributor in Asia (WPI Group、SAC Group、RichPower Group、Pernas Group、AIT Group、YOSUN Group, andAECO Group) serves as a franchise partner for near 250 world-wide brands (over 300 brands for Non-Exclusive Agency ). With 6,500 staff over 130 sales offices around the world (about 80 around Greater China and Asia Pacific region), WPG Holdings sales is over US$12.2billion in 2012(unaudited).</p>\r\n<div>\r\n\t<br />\r\n\tWPG continues to outdistance its rivals as the largest industrial distributor in Asia and perhaps more significantly, is rated the best semiconductor distributor in Asia by both customers and suppliers. In the latest issue of Forbes, WPG Holdings ranked The Forbes Global 2000 List in 2012. The synergy of consolidation emerged from the establishment of WPG Holdings in Nov. 2005. Based on profit growth and operating asset efficiency improvement, ROE and Return on Working Capital (ROWC) has improved respectively 11.9% and 10.4% in 2012(unaudited). EPS was NT$2.73. With our vision of &ldquo;The First Choice of Industry, The Benchmark of Distribution.&rdquo;, WPG Holdings has been elevated to rank within the top three IC component distributors worldwide</div>\r\n",
